servings: 2
---

Preheat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Cut the @onion{1} in half through the root, peel and chop into small ½cm pieces. Remove the top and bottom from the @courgette{1}, cut in half lengthways, then cut into 1cm wide strips. Chop each strip into 1cm chunks. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one).

Pop a deep ovenproof #saucepan{} on medium heat and add a drizzle of oil and your onion. Cook for ~{5%minutes} until your onion is soft, then add your courgette and cook for another ~{5%minutes}. Stir in your garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @risotto rice{175%g}.

Stir your rice into your garlicky oil and cook for ~{1%minute} until the edges are slightly translucent, then add the @white wine vinegar{1}. Cook until your vinegar has evaporated, then add the @water{400%ml} along with the @vegetable stock pot{1} and a good grind of @black pepper{}.

Stir everything together and bring to the boil, making sure your stock pot has dissolved. Pop a #lid{} on (or some #tinfoil{} tightly covering the pan), then put your risotto on the top shelf of your oven to bake for ~{20%minutes}.

> Tip: If your pan isn't ovenproof, just pour the mixture into an ovenproof dish and cover tightly with tinfoil instead.

While your risotto bakes, make your pesto. Roughly chop the @Brazil nuts{25}(roughly chopped) and finely chop the @basil{1}(finely chopped). Finely chop a quarter of the @wild rocket{1}(finely chopped). Pop your Brazil nuts, basil, chopped rocket and @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} into a #bowl{} with the @olive oil{3%tbsp}. Grind in some black pepper and mix it together.

Cut the @goat's cheese{1} into 1cm thick slices (you should have four slices per person).

Once your risotto is ready, remove it from your oven. Preheat your #grill{} to high. Stir your pesto into your risotto, then flatten it out in the pan. Place your goat's cheese on top of your risotto and then pop it under your grill for ~{4-5%minutes} until your goat's cheese has browned.

While your risotto is grilling, pop the remaining rocket into a bowl and drizzle in a little olive oil. Add a small squeeze of @lemon{1/2}(squeezed) and toss together. Taste and add more lemon juice if you feel it needs it.

Remove your risotto from your grill and serve in #bowls{} with a handful of rocket on top. Enjoy!